<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Excite Plans Wireless Web Content </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	REDWOOD CITY, Calif. (AP) -- AirFlash Inc., a mobile Internet  
provider, announced today an agreement to make ExciteAtHome's Web 
content available through mobile devices such as cellular phones. 
</P>
<P>
	AirFlash provides cellular phone companies with the technology  
to set up portal sites accessible by cellular phones. AirFlash's 
Mobile Portal technology will use ExciteAtHome's content and 
services, such as e-mail and schedule planners. 
</P>
<P>
	AirFlash provides its own content -- local Yellow Pages, events  
and attractions, travel advisories, scheduling and booking -- 
allowing mobile phone users to access information through a series 
of menus. 
</P>
<P>
	ExciteAtHome Corp., based in Redwood City, has been working to  
make its content available through a wide variety of devices -- from 
television sets to handheld information devices. 
</P>
<P>
	Competitor America Online Inc. is following a similar track with  
its ``AOL Anywhere'' strategy that allows AOL's 17 million 
customers to link up with the service no matter where they are. 
</P>
<P>
	AirFlash, a privately held company, is also based in Redwood  
City. ExciteAtHome operates the sixth-most visited site on the Web, 
according to Internet measurement company Media Metrix. 



</P>
</TEXT>
