<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Charged With Larceny in Hoax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- A woman claiming to have ovarian cancer raised  
thousands of dollars for cancer research, then used the money to 
buy herself a car and have liposuction, prosecutors said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kristen Clougherty, 24, raised as much as $50,000 in the past  
year from friends, family and other donors, said Suffolk County 
District Attorney Ralph C. Martin II. 
</P>
<P>
	She even organized the ``First Annual Kristen Clougherty 5K  
Run/Walk'' to benefit her cancer fund-raising efforts -- even though 
investigators were unable to find any evidence she has cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	Clougherty faces a charge of larceny over $250. No one answered  
a phone call placed to her home on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ovarian Cancer Research Fund Executive Director Jamie Boris said  
he was ``deeply upset'' about Clougherty's alleged activities. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is very distressing that our good name would be used for an  
alleged illegal fund-raising activity,'' he said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
