<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> VW Marks its 100 Millionth Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BERLIN (AP) -- Volkswagen celebrated its 100 millionth car  
Tuesday -- a silver ``New Beetle'' made in Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Board member Klaus Kocks said the jubilee car was a symbol of  
how far Europe's biggest automaker has come since the company's 
beginnings with the 1938 introduction of the original Volkswagen. 
</P>
<P>
	VW marked the event with a street party at the famed Brandenburg  
Gate in the heart of Berlin. 
</P>
<P>
	The New Beetle, launched last year, has been a hit in the United  
States but has yet to take off in Europe. With its bug-eyed 
headlights and rounded roof, it's meant to meld the original's 
shapes with up-do-date technology. 
</P>
<P>
	Born under Adolf Hitler's guidance, the Volkswagen -- German for  
``people's car'' -- was meant to offer affordable transportation for 
the nation, modeled on what Henry Ford had done for Americans. 
</P>
<P>
	The VW plant in Wolfsburg was rebuilt after being destroyed by  
Allied bombs in World War II, and the hardy car went on to become a 
worldwide success. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
