<HEADLINE> Six Boys Suspected in Gang Rape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- Six boys, ages 5 to 13, are suspected in  
an attack on an 8-year-old girl who police say was forced into an 
abandoned house and gang-raped. 
</P>
<P>
	The attack occurred on Sept. 7 or 8 but wasn't reported to  
police until last week by the victim's mother, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl was playing outside her home when she was attacked.  
Four of the six suspects raped her, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Her brother heard her cries for help and tried to come to her  
aid, but at least two of the suspects stopped him. He then left to 
get an older brother, who was able to rescue her, said police 
spokesman Michael Jordan. 
</P>
<P>
	No arrests have been made, but three suspects were questioned at  
an elementary school Monday morning and the others were being 
sought. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl apparently knew her attackers. ``They may not have been  
friends, but they weren't absolute strangers,'' Jordan said. ``It 
doesn't appear that it was random.'' 
  	   	
