<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Pistons Trade Draft Pick for Harper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Pistons traded the rights  
to their top draft pick, Melvin Levett, to the Los Angeles Lakers 
for veteran Derek Harper Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Levett, a 6-foot-3 guard who played at Cincinnati, was the 54th  
overall pick in the June draft. 
</P>
<P>
	The 37-year-old Harper will back up starting point guard Lindsey  
Hunter. 
</P>
<P>
	``Derek gives us the backup point guard we've been looking  
for,'' Pistons General Manager Rick Sund said. ``He's been in the 
league for 16 seasons and has played at a high level his entire 
career.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Harper has also played for the Mavericks, New York Knicks and  
Orlando Magic. He has averaged 13.3 points and 5.5 assists in 1,119 
career games, eighth on the NBA's all-time list. 
</P>
<P>
	Harper is seventh on the NBA's career steals list with 1,957,  
and is 10th all-time with 3,026 3-point field goal attempts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
