<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Oil Co. Finds New Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) -- Brazilian oil giant Petrobras has  
discovered new oil reserves in the offshore Santos Basin estimated 
at between 600 million and 700 million barrels, Mines and Energy 
Minister Rodolpho Tourinho announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	He said the field has ``ultralight'' oil, which is considered of  
excellent quality. The field, located off the coast of Rio de 
Janeiro state, is in an area Petrobras has been prospecting since 
1971. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement came as foreign companies are beginning to  
operate in Brazil for the first time after the government ended an 
almost 50-year monopoly held by Petrobras. 
</P>
<P>
	President Fernando Henrique Cardoso said total potential  
reserves are worth $10 billion. 
  	   	
</P>
