<HEADLINE> Pioneering Colt Brings in $160K </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- A son of Pioneering brought the top price  
of $160,000 during Tuesday's session of the Keeneland September 
Yearling Sale. 
</P>
<P>
	Eric Reed, as agent for Charles Kurtsinger, bought the chestnut  
colt from Iron County Farms Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Pioneering, a son of Mr. Prospector, is a half-brother to  
leading sire Storm Cat. His first foals are yearlings this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Second high price of the day was $150,000 paid by Dale Romans,  
as agent, for a bay colt by Silver Ghost. Douglas S. Arnold's Buck 
Pond Farm, as agent, sold the colt. 
</P>
<P>
	Keeneland sold 304 horses for $6,332,800 during Tuesday's  
session. The average was $20,832. During the corresponding session 
last year, 288 horses brought $4,001,200, an average of $13,893. 
</P>
<P>
	With two days remaining in the 11-day auction, 2,505 horses have  
sold for $227,335,200, an average of $90,753. Last year, 2,611 
horses had been sold for $167,364,100, an average of $64,100. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
