<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Credit Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Compared with 27 percent of whites with bad credit:  
</P>
<P>
	--47 percent of blacks have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--34 percent of Hispanics have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	Among people with incomes under $25,000:  
</P>
<P>
	--36 percent of all respondents have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--48 percent of blacks have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--31 percent of whites have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--39 percent of Hispanics have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--22 percent of Asians have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	Among people with incomes of $65,000 to $75,000:  
</P>
<P>
	--21 percent of all respondents have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--34 percent of blacks have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--20 percent of whites have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--27 percent of Hispanics have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	--12 percent of Asians have bad credit.  
</P>
<P>
	Bad credit is defined as those where consumers have been either  
90 days late on a payment in the last two years, 30 days late on a 
payment more than once in the last two years or have a record of 
delinquent liens, public records or a bankruptcy. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
