<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-21 17:40:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Encad Cites Hewlett-Packard in Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Hewlett-Packard Corp. has been ordered to  
temporarily stop offering jumbo-sized color inkjet printers at 
below cost through its trade-in program pending trial of a lawsuit 
that accuses the computer maker of driving out the competition. 
</P>
<P>
	Encad had sued H-P earlier this year, saying the company was  
violating the California Unfair Trade Practices Act and the Unfair 
Competition law by allowing customers to pay nothing if the value 
of a printer that is traded in is more than the cost of an H-P 
printer, said Ronald S. Katz, a lawyer for Encad. 
</P>
<P>
	``If they sell below cost, that is a problem. It may help the  
consumer in the short term. In the long run you get rid of 
competition and H-P can raise prices,'' Katz said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	San Francisco Superior Court Judge David Garcia on Friday  
ordered H-P to halt the trade in program pending the outcome of the 
trial, which was scheduled to begin in January. 
</P>
<P>
	Encad has lost at least $50 million because of the trade-in  
program, Katz said. Encad could be awarded as much as $150 million 
in damages, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Susan Murdy, a Hewlett-Packard spokeswoman in San Jose, said the  
company will comply with the court's order. 
</P>
<P>
	Hewlett-Packard is confident that ``a fuller examination'' will  
show the company has complied with California law, Murdy said in a 
statement. She declined to elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	Hewlett-Packard is the world's largest supplier of inkjet  
printers. The company won't disclose how much it makes on those 
sales, though analysts say H-P probably earns more on printer 
supplies than on the printers themselves. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's hard to say what the ruling is going to do,'' said Paula  
Bursley, senior industry analyst at Dataquest Inc. ``The objective 
of the business itself is to make the money off the supplies. 
Hardware is really a secondary thing.'' 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
